HEADWORD: a.u.
<hw>a.u.</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn><fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>the
unit of length equal to the mean distance of the Earth from the sun,
about 93 million miles (150 million kilometers); -- used almost
exclusively in astronomy, or to describe astronomical
distances.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> astronomical unit, AU, A.U.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

